<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>31-5607.08</num>
  <heading>Provisions applicable to administrative proceedings.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>All actions of the Commissioner, including administrative proceedings, adoption of rules, and issuance of orders shall be governed by <cite path="2|5|I">subchapter I of Chapter 5 of Title 2</cite>; provided, that:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>The issuance of a stop order under <cite path="§31-5603.03|(e)">§ 31-5603.03(e)</cite> shall be governed by <cite path="§31-5603.03|(e)">§ 31-5603.03(e)</cite>; and</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>The issuance of a summary order under <cite path="§31-5606.02|(a)">§ 31-5606.02(a)</cite> shall be governed by <cite path="§31-5606.02|(a)">§ 31-5606.02(a)</cite>.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 13-203" type="History" path="§708">Oct. 26, 2000, D.C. Law 13-203, § 708, 47 DCR 7837</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
